Track recent visitors to your website or blog - embed on your iGoogle page or on your website or blog.
WikiMapia is a project to describe the whole planet Earth. Done as a community-built geographic WikiPedia. Just move the map to find interesting places, click on rectangles, create your own.

Great use of the Amazon toolkit by Jim Bumgardner to combine hundreds of similar Amazon product images merged into a single interactive page. You can buy from here or use his banners in your own site.
Using carpark information and map information from OneMotoring.com.sg and Google Maps respectively, users can have a birds-eye view of all the parking costs in Singapore.

CoverSlide helps track down lost cover art for mp3s, movies, books, and video games. Ruby on Rails and Ajax make it convenient to select from a vast amount of cover art thumbnails to choose the perfect one without leaving the page.
Mashes up articles from several marketplaces like ebay, Amazon or ricardo.ch, a Swiss auction platform, and displays it on a map. Uses Ip Geo-Information to display initial map view.
Spendfish uses the Amazon API to find deals on amazon.com.
The latest worldwide stories from the Washington Post plotted on a Google Maps satellite image.

column1: Mashup: New 7 Wonders of the World
column5: New 7 Wonders of the world mapped on Google Maps along with YouTube video for each of the 7 wonder.

A better search for Flickr. Uses special processing to find for more than just what you search for. Searching for music will not just look for that word but also for concert, band, ipod and other related concepts.
Good use of Yahoo! Maps + Flickr to show CalTrain route and schedule data with station photos.
Generative fiction with Google Maps and Flickr.
Predict Alexa rankings in this stock market simulation game.
A Google Maps view of the 50 most expensive cities in the world as surveyed by Mercer Human Resource Consulting.
Save some money, get the latest deals from SecretPrices.com right on your cell phone via SMS, email or WAP. Configure alerts and get notified as new deals are posted.
Like tinyurl, but for maps. Create a map, add routes or points of interest, and get a short URL to share it or come back to it later.
Weather and climate information for Africa visualized on Google Maps.
A visually rich application that combines the Amazon API to show the relationship between movies, bands, actors, etc. You can go straight from interacting to making purchases.
YouTube meets Google Maps. A real estate listings service that streams videos of properties on sale inside Google map
Livecontacts friend finder application for connected Windows Mobile PDAs and Nokia Symbian smartphones. Know where your friends are and plot your position in Google Maps.
column6: ['Google Maps', 'Microsoft MapPoint', 'Microsoft Bing Maps', 'MSN Messenger', 'Map24 AJAX']

column5: eBay API application the gives fast Flash-based search results on a map but is useful for being more search than map. Sliders above map show items on criteria such a price, bids, time, and distance.

Virtualtraveller aims to supply the user relevant information about some location on earth of his/her choosing. To accomplish this, this site makes heavy use of various web services and data including Wikipedia, Google, Flickr and Youtube.
column6: ['Flickr', 'Google Maps', 'YouTube', 'NOAA National Weather Service (NWS) NDFD SOAP', 'Yahoo Geocoding', 'GeoNames', 'Google AdSense']

column5: Zuckerbucks are points that you can use like play money on Facebook. They have no cash value, but you can send them to friends as gifts, or as payment. You can also bid on real products featured within the Zuckerbucks app.
A collection of stuff to do with Flickr image manipulation, community based photo search engine and a system to print photos on shirts, mugs, and stickers.
A democratic approach to search. You can search the internet, vote for a particular result and also comment on a particular site.
Generative fictives biographies. Search picture memories in Flickr.
Reskin your iGoogle page and share your skins with others by submitting to the directory.
Google maps and a "shout" site that has a "Roaming geek", find the Geek and shout any message you want on any location on the map.

Great mashup: video of racing through Paris in one window while course is drawn realtime on a map in another. In 1978 filmmaker Claude Lelouch put a gyro-stabilized camera on a Ferrari 275 GTB with a professional Formula 1 racer drive at breakneck speed.
Using the FeedBurner API this tool draws a graph of your sites feedreaders over a period of time.
Learn a lot about your web site with this mashup. Check the incoming links, the directories a domain is in, its PageRank, and more with this domain-info script.
Compare two images and pick the winner in this HotOrNot-style voting mashup. See pairs of photos of men, women, cars, cats, dogs and more. Note: some photos not safe for work, NSFW.

A generative artwork that explores how advertising uses and manipulates language. Real corporate slogans are remixed and randomized to generate invented slogans, then paired with Flickr images, generating fake advertisements on the fly.
Price comparison and shopping portal website.
Makes Tribe.net forums mobile. Read latest posts on the Tribe forums on your cell phone using SMS, WAP and e-mail. Use the keyword tribe and provide the tribe name.
Provides a list of videos, pictures, maps, and wikipedia information for Forbes traveler's list of top 50 locations.
Job search site that will plot job locations on a Google Map.

Plazes adds physical presence to the web. The Plazes website automatically detects your location and connects you to people and places nearby. See people in your area, discover other locations and follow the whereabouts of your friends.
Mobile GMaps is an application that displays Google Maps, Yahoo Maps, Windows Live Local and Ask.com Maps and satellite imagery on Java J2ME-enabled mobile phones, PDAs and other devices.
Shopping made faster at Compare4.us. A mashup of several shopping APIs to allow users a broader search with one interface.
Virginia Beach and Norfolk area rental ads with syndication to Google Base, Oodle, VAST and Edgeio.
Flickr photos + Yahoo! Maps. Click on a city to see your Flickr contacts and then hover over icons to get details.
Share your location in real-time using Mologogo. A free service that will track your friends GPS-enabled cell phones from another phone or on the web. With various social networking features.
Share your cycling, walking, hiking, and paddling routes with the world. See maps, photos, and stats about each route, or create your own.
Create, update, and track your business plan with your entire team and export out a document version at any time.
A service that calls you on your cell phone so you can bid and win eBay auctions in the last 3 minutes.
Washington DC city and transit guide Google Maps mashup. Metro Links also combines blog postings from Window Shopper, Free Ride and Top Stops.

column1: Mashup: Realtime Stock Quotes by Phone
column5: Get real time stock quotes of your favorite stocks n your mobile phone using SMS, WAP or Email. Use the keyword quote followed by the ticker symbol. Provide multiple ticker symbols, like quote goog yhoo.

Winner of the 2007 ETel Mashup Contest. A clever and useful mashup that transcribes office voice mails left by patients for doctors into text and then sends them via SMS to the doctor. With source code.

column1: Mashup: Tour de France Tracking in Realtime
column5: Track the progress of the 2007 Tour de France with this real-time tracking map.
Easy to use tool to build a street map showing one location, eg. location of a business.
Create sets of media related to fashion, particularly leaning towards coverage of fashion events, and share them with other members.
View reviews of stores, restaurants, bars and venues placed in context on a Google Map.
Mashup of Google Map and Yahoo RSS Feeds
loc.alize.us displays a massive amount of photos on a highly interactive world map. Explore photos from everyones places, selected topics or people you know.
Geology.com uses Google Maps satellite images for exploring several of earth's meteor impact craters.

Create a scrapbook, family album, or other physical book using this web-based creation tool. Lets you integrate photos from Flickr. Click Start Book and then the Demo MemoryPress link to view a video that shows the mashup of Flickr and a user book.

column1: Mashup: Top 10 African Americans in Hollywood
column5: Black Enterprise magazine listing of Top 10 Most Powerful Blacks in Hollywood, mapped by place of birth with biographical info and videos.
A Google Maps mashup for finding golf courses in Germany with course details and simple rating. Enter a German zip or a German city to check it out, eg. Munich.

Life2Life is a real store in a virtual world. Uses the Amazon and SecondLife APIs to allow you to shop in virtual space. This link brings you to the story about it, you need Second Life to see it in action.
Uses the Amazon E-Commerce API to create a clean, simple interface to the Amazon catalog.

column1: Mashup: on AIR Bus Tracking Map
column5: Map to show you the current location of the Adobe on AIR promotional tour bus.

column1: Mashup: Top 25 Crimes of the Century
column5: The top 25 crimes as reported by Time magazine are plotted on a map with useful information and photos about each.

column1: Mashup: ocarto a meta map mashup
column5: Cool way to create and save your own hybrid maps using several mapping APIs. This mashup layers Google, Yahoo, MS Virtual Earth, and Terraserver maps into one interface - similar to the way Photoshop layers work.
PHP source code for combining Salesforce.com and Google Maps. Note: suitable only if you are a Salesforce customer.
Upload your GPS tracks stored in GPX format, and see your tracks and your friends tracks in satellite view.
Watch the data that you care about in this screensaver mashup of Facebook, Flickr, Twitter, and blogs. This visualization lets you configure what you want to watch and the speed in which you see it.
This mashup plots US Environmental Protection Agency data on a Google Map. Ability to search by location.
Fun game where you have to guess which WashingtonPost arts and entertainment story images came from which categories. From Adam DuVander.
Slick music information mashup with photos, videos and news. Search or browse artists by name or genre.
Tools for optimizing product sales on eBay.

Lots of handy tools that let you profile any the 87,058,540 Internet domains in existence. In addition to indexing every active domain, it also knows about the 237,192,827 inactive domains that have been registered and deleted since the early days.
Interactive Google Map of the Montreal subway system with links to the Montreal Transit Website.
The Internet TV charts tracks the most popular online video clips each week from four leading Internet TV sites. All the best video clips, on one page.
Online tool to generate code for Google and Yahoo maps. Does not required knowledge of the APIs or JavaScript. Share your own maps and explore maps created by others.
Wide collection of Arabic media including TV, radio, movies and clips.

column1: Mashup: Find Airport Delays by Phone
column5: Get real time airport departure and arrival delays before heading to the airport. Get this information on WAP, SMS or Email. Use the keyword delays followed by the airport code, i.e. SFO, ATL etc.
Search Zooomr tags from your cell phone. Get a list of upto 10 photos on your WAP capable mobile device.
User-edited search results for health, beauty and fashion sites plus blog, friends, reviews and contests.

Get the toll free number for any airline on the go, when not in front of your PC. Get this information using SMS, WAP or email. Use the keyword airline followed by the part of the airline name, Eg: united, south, northwest

A Google guessing game. Look at this montage of images from Google Image Search and try to guess what keyword make up the image.
Draws musical scales on a virtual fretboard. Uses the FUTEF API to get scale information from Wikipedia.
Flash-based interface to Google Talk. Allows you to chat without a client install. Gtalkr also has its own API.
Maps postal codes to geographical coordinates and shows them on a map.
At GPSies.com, you can view and download tracks that have been recorded by a GPS device. Search for running, hiking, and biking routes. You can download all of the tracks.
Free, self-serve carpool or rideshare commuter matching service. Map-centric with user-friendly interface.
An auto-tagging service that allows sites to add their own tag clouds.
HYDESim maps the potential effects of radii generated by a ground-level nuclear detonation.
Comprehensive searchable gazeteer based on Google Maps. Referenc guide has full world coverage.
Google Maps Mashup of vacation and travel information in Germany.
Locate ping-pong tables in Berlin, Germany, on a map.
Orginalsignal.com aggregates the 15 most popular web 2.0 weblogs like TechCrunch, ReadWriteWeb, Solution Watch, 37signals, eHub, GigaOM etc.
Collection site where users can post things they collect, have, or want to trade. Uses RapLeaf as a feedback and reputation system.
Create your own slideshow and let it run on your Netvibes homepage. Numerous styles and effects available. Go to imageloop.com, upload your photos, and fetch your Slideshow-URL.
Listing of UK pubs with reviews and ability to have a Google Map generated based a city with starting and ending bars.
Customizable maps, fishing catch tracker, fishing reports and daily weather.
column6: ['Google Search', 'Google Maps', 'NOAA National Weather Service (NWS) NDFD SOAP']

column5: Get real time listings from Windows Expo Live on your cell phone, using SMS, Email and WAP. Just send us the zip code for the location and what you are looking for, i.e. product details.

column1: Mashup: Yahoo! APIs Example with Code
column5: Example Yahoo! Map with overlay of Local and Traffic information. With link to article on how this was programmed. By Dan Theurer.
Stockaholic uses the EditGrid dynamic images to mashup charts from Yahoo Finance. See the Instructions tab to see how to do it.

column1: Mashup: Yellow Pages plus Denver Health Inspections
column5: See health code violations and past inspections directly on a restaurant listing page.
Find mashed up maps in your locale: city, state, country, or the world, sorted by categories. Updated daily with your suggestions.
Mashup of Google Maps and Southern California high tech and startup venture funding.
Mashup satellite images from BBC Weather and t7online. See the Instructions tab to see how to do it.

column1: Mashup: Citysearch meets Denver Health Inspections
column5: Mashup of the Citysearch.com local search and review site with the Denver restaurant health inspections database. See health code violations and past inspections directly on a restaurant listing page.
Interactive Google Map showing pubs in London with reviews.
Google News Bar gadget (based on Google AJAX search API) can be added to your Google home page. Add the search terms of your interest and view them as vertical or horizontal newsbars.
Mashup of Google Maps and Rocky Mountain venture capital investments

Maps restaurants in Toronto. Use check boxes below the map to select from Indian, Chinese, Sushi, and so on, and then click the Show Selection button to map the restaurants of those types. Click a location to view a short description.
Guide for businesses and service providers in Switzerland with community integration.

WikiWalki lets you search, draw, and share your favorite outdoor trail by importing and exporting GPS data and Google mapping them. Use it to email a cool map of your walk, bike ride or running trail to your friends or find a new hike or city tour nearby.

column1: Mashup: AP National News + Google Maps
column5: A simple mashup that plots stories from the AP National News RSS feed on a Google Map. The Yahoo! Geocode API is used to convert the location of each story to a longitude/latitude point. Currently, only the U.S./National news stories are plotted.
Karaoke2U is the user and YouTube powered content site for your Karaoke Videos. All Video is submitted and voted on by the Karaoke2U community. Share, watch and promote your Karaoke Videos.

400 virtual images of places to visit on the island of Sardinia, Italy. See 360 degree panoramas of historical sites, resorts, coastlines, and countryside. Where to stay, what to do, events, and festivals.
Chinese Google Maps mashup that allow people to share maps.
Google Power Search exposes Google search features like search by file type.
TubeBattle is a community-driven video rating system. Includes sexy video section which is probably NSFW, not safe for work.

column1: Mashup: Metro System in Naples, Italy
column5: View the lines and stops of the metro system in Naples, Italy.

Twitter mashed-up with Del.icio.us & Ma.gnolia.com. When you are viewing your or a friends timeline, you have the option to clip the tweet. This saves the tweet URL tweet in your bookmark account as a private link with a specific tag so you view it later.

This widget will display the latest items from the Digg website. You can change its preferences to point to change the minimum number of diggs and count of displayed items. More than just RSS, it displays both the item content and images.
Google Maps mashup with searchable US Golf Courses, weather data and details golf course information.
Save on shipping with this Yahoo Maps + eBay mashup to show auctions within your local zip code.

Bookmark Cleaner helps you keep you del.icio.us or ma.gnolia.com bookmarks clean. It allows searches: A malware and phishing site search A search for cleaning bookmarks with a particular tag and a search for links that no longer exist, aka 404 not found.
Create, save and share personal customizable Google maps. Easy to share links to sites, or embed map in web page. RSS feed for newly published maps.
Mashup with searchable US Golf Courses, weather data and details golf course information.
Musipedia, The Open Music Encyclopedia, uses Amazon Alexa to provide the ability to search the web by melody. Give the engine a keyword or melodic contour, and it returns similar music.
Elkx-Box means embeddable multilingual keyword extraction box and provides a way to embed a box on your web page containing all relevant keywords of your content.The whole service is free of charge.

Used cars and new car shopping site with extensive use of APIs. Yahoo Map Image is used to get around the https issue with Google Maps. YouTube drives the video search. Users can leave a car review, an article, or a dealer review.
Search for city properties and view listings via Google Maps.
Online running log service with local search and sharing using Google maps. Running log has nice graphing features.

This mashup modifies CNN articles, integrating the Congressional voting history, campaign finance history, etc. for members of the House and Senate mentioned in the page text. This mashes up CNN.com and the Pop-up Politicians widget from Sunlight Labs.
Meta search tool from a group of students at Allegheny College. Results from many search engines and social services.
Take a tour on a world map to see all of our pets and their locations.
A straightforward and clean interface to YouTube via their APIs. Workplace safe.

column1: Mashup: My Pet Profile on iGoogle
column5: Add My Pet Profile from MatchMyPet.com to your iGoogle page.

column1: Mashup: World Airport and Airspace Database
column5: Database of over 11,000 airfields and airports across the world, from major internationals like New York, Paris and London to more out-of the way airstrips like Antartica.
A nice way to see the any location side-by-side in Google and Yahoo Maps. Even dragging one map drags the other.
A mash-up of the most creative videos found on Google Video, YouTube, Blip.tv and other video sharing sites.

column1: Mashup: If I Dig Straight Down
column5: Everyone in the US knows that if you dig straight down you end up in China. Except you will not, but instead will end up swimming. Use this dual map tool to see where you go if you dig.
Create you own winery tour! Mashup of U.S. wineries, winery events, wine festivals, and wine trails. Over 3,200 entries. Includes printable Google directions with full winery contact information.

This Google Maps mashup lets you see an outline of one part of the world overlayed on another part of the world. For example, you can sketch an outline of New Jersey in the Reference Map then overlay the outline over Japan in the Comparison Map.
Add your pets to your Facebook profile page.
Real estate portal in Dubai. Uses Google Maps for mapping and Amazon S3 for image storage.
Real estate listings from eBay plotted on a Google Map.
Satellite images, information and directions for hundreds of stadiums across the United States.
Tracking campaign appearances by major candidates. In French.
Mapping community site that lets users create and save maps consisting of waypoints and routes.
A dynamic network feed of geo-tagged Flickr photos in Google Earth.

5th Bar is a new way to avoid getting the wrong phone again. Find and share reviews and information about mobile phones, cell phone carriers, and accessories. Mashup content from YouTube, eBay, Amazon, and CNET.
A jukebox-like playlist for YouTube videos. No need to listen to your own MP3s when YouTube already has everything online.
A hot-or-not style dance rating site based on YouTube videos tagged dance.

A Google map based interactive guide to the Bournemouth, Dorset, UK area. The map shows attractions, food outlets, pubs, and clubs. Routes mode lets you plot journeys and calculate distances. History mode displays a map of old local photos.
Helps children learn the English alphabet through photos.
Stats and summaries of the top videos on YouTube, by day, week, and month. Also, read a mashup tutorial on the How I Built It page.
A virtual tour of New York City using AJAX and Google Maps. Navigate through the streets of New York using thousands of pictures, viewing hundreds of descriptions and details on history.

column1: Mashup: Latest Fashionwire Photos on Phone
column5: View the latest photos from Fashiowire on your WAP capable phone. Fire up your mobile browser and point to http://411sync.com. Simply use the keyword fashionwire.
Real time Google maps of current parking availability in the San Francisco Bay Area.
Use the MyShopping application for Facebook to connect with friends, co-workers, or family on your daily shopping activities.
Find useful information about Singapore places

Mashup showing locations of 200 places mentioned in the Bible. Going for accuracy they try to pinpoint the locations of the ruins of ancient cities instead of using the locations of modern cities with ancient names.
Music mashup that pulls in data from iTunes, Amazon, YouTube, and ticketing sites to provide a full music experience. Login required.

PackageMapper shows you a map of your FedEx, UPS, USPS package routes. Enter a carrier and a tracking number to see your package's progress plotted on the map. Sign in to enter a list of packages and see their current locations on a table or map.
Full featured commercial service to track contact data, notes and history. Free level allows 500 contacts. Integrates with Skype, S3 and Alexa Thumbnail services.
View geolocalized del.icio.us bookmarks over a 3D earth globe. Search by tag or username.

Millions of Flickr photos have been geotagged and placed on a Yahoo Map. Uses the recently added Geo features of Flickr. Add a special tag for photos from Upcoming.org events and they will be linked to that page automatically.
Service for you to collect, organize, and share information for shopping, travel or any other research.
Apartment listings in NYC with Google Maps.
Follow World Cup Cricket in real time on your phone using SMS, WAP or email. Use the keyword cricscore and get back results of ongoing matches.
B2B integration looking to deliver the benefits of ahigh-transaction-charge value-added-network, a VAN, without high on-going transaction fees. Built on Amazon Simple Queue and Storage services.
Gothamist Maps are a great way to see what is going on and where right now in NYC.
Search eBay and see your results laid out on a Google Map.
A tag-based search engine that combines results from Flickr, delicious, Technorati and Google News.
Get BBC news headlines via Twitter.
Click on two points on the NYC Google Map and the program will display the shortest subway route between those two points, including walking time.
Rich visualizations, metrics, and stats for Digg. Get charts by category, user, and time.
Synchronize Microsoft Outlook and Google Calendar with this Windows utility. Requires .Net 2.0 and Outlook 2003 or higher.

A map of contributions to 2006 Massachusetts gubernatorial campaigns. Uses the Google Maps API and data from the Massachusetts Office of Campaign and Political finance. One of the most extensive use of data with layering on Google Maps.

column1: Mashup: Birds of Central Park Map
column5: Very nice map featuring locations of photos from the book Birds of Central Park.

Consolidation of information about notable people, including celebrities, musicians, writers, historical figures and sports people. Auto-ranking of people based on density of current news and automatic analysis of connections between people.
Motorcycle roads, routes and rides, with interactive road maps and scenic photography.
Simple tool for adding an interactive store locator mapping to your website
Displays volcanos of the world on a Google Map. Data from the Smithsonian Institution, Global Vulcanism Project
Search and display multiple items, add notes to specific items and call sellers with single click directly from item listings, if seller number is in item listing.

column1: Mashup: Boulder Library with Amazon Reviews
column5: See Amazon.com customer reviews and editorials within the online card catalog of the Boulder, Colo., public library.
A youtube clone with added ability to download the video source from server to PC.
A website plagiarism search tool that uses the Google Search API.
Listen to songs from your Pandora stations and see music from those artists ready to buy without leaving the page.

column1: Mashup: BBB Lookups in Judys Book
column5: Mashup of the local search site Judys Book with Denver-area Better Business Bureau business lookups and a search within the city contractor database for a valid contractor license.

Dunkathon is a HotOrNot version of basketball dunking clips. Videos are retrieved by filtering clips from YouTube API and only keep the ones that are relevant to dunking and short in length, 40 sec or less.
See the location of elaborate Christmas lights displays. Readers can add comments and vote for favorites.

searchCrystal lets you search and visually compare multiple engines in one place. It is a search visualization tool for remixing and sharing results from the best web, image, video, blog, tagging, news engines as well as Flickr images or RSS feeds.

column1: Mashup: Judys Book meets Better Business Bureau
column5: New and improved mashup of Judys Book local search and the Better Bureau Search websites for more than 20 major metropolitan areas and a number of states and locales.
Send and receive SMS text messages from Microsoft Outlook. Get Outlook appointment reminders and important messages forwarded to your phone.

This map shows all UK trains currently on approach to a particular station. Data is fetched from the National Rail website. The yellow pins are stations, the red pins trains. The trains move in approximately real time.
It's a non-commercial city portal with a Google Mgap of Torun, a beatiful, medieval Polish town.

This mashup uses 2000 Census data and Google Maps. Each zip is color coded by population density. Adding a lot of cities to the map makes it resemble election results. There's also a search function to see where your hometown ranks with other cities.
Search Google and Yahoo at the same time.
Video surveillance system allowing you to monitor and broadcast images of your home or office to the Internet or a mobile phone.
Music Codex allows you to create a music collection virtual shelf.
UK site with Google Maps to help find dine-in and takeaway food. Menus and readers reviews online to peruse.
Great visualization of Google and Yahoo search. Type in a search and see a graph connecting the matching results across the search engines.
Find bargains on Amazon.com. Find items by highest percentage off, popularity, rating and bargains.
Makes it easy to post your current location to Twitter so that it's picked up by Twittervision. Zero signup using OpenID.
Find beer and more with this comprehensive listing and map of retail establishments in Toronto and the rest of Ontario.
Hotel World Map lets you search and book 60.000 hotels worldwide on an interactive Google Map. From charminging hotels on the Spanish coast to business hotel close to the conference centres.
Schedule SMS reminders for events up to 18 months in advance.
Search multiple photo sharing sites. Has technology that quantifies colors like red or blue in images, making it possible to show search results by color. Search phrases like: red flower in spring.

School Performance Maps provides a bird's eye view of public school performance in California. Data from California Department of Education, Academic Performance Index. The 1-10 is statewide rank school, low to high.
This Google Maps transit mashup takes an independent ride-guide for the San Diego Trolley and mashes it up with Google Maps.
Community-based meta search engine that allows users to collaborate, discuss, tag, and link aggregated search results.
Watch your favorite TV shows on tv3o.com. A source for TV shows, photos, episode guides, cast, reviews, community, merchandise, and more.
Google Map of the London Underground.
Shows the results of Indeed job search on a Google Map.
Generate a tag cloud from music artists similar to the one you submit. Use it find find new bands you like. Including YouTube music videos.
Rate basketball dunk video clips from YouTube.

column1: Mashup: Looqy for eBay and Amazon
column5: Search eBay listings then browse through them in a single page. Add notes to individual listings for later reference. Call sellers directly from the web-site by clicking on a button.

Peer-to-peer collaboration engine built on the Skype API that converts mainstream productivity applications such as the Microsoft Office suite from static standalone tools to interactive, collaborative platforms.
Plots the hometowns of the top American Idol contestants.
50 random World Heritage Sites on a Google Map. Each time you reload it shows another 50 random sites. With embedded photos and links to details on each site.
Watch twitters in real time with this live map that dynamically updates to show the latest twitterings.
deliSearch allows you to do a Yahoo search through a delicious users bookmark collection. Think Rollyo, with search rolls from delicious.

Get the latest college football headlines on your mobile phone using SMS, WAP and Email. These headlines are obtained from Rivals.com. Use the keyword rivals followed by the state, i.e. ca, wa, az etc.
Crime mapping site for Leawood, Kansas.
Amazon books combined with Windows Live Local. It allows users to find books on Amazon based upon geographical locations around the world.

Texsy automatically underlines product-y phrases on a web page, and creates a mouseover ad with related products and prices. The ad clicks are connected to the Amazon, Ebay and Shopping.com affiliate programs.
Create your own custom iheart, I Love X, shirts, buttons, and bumper stickers at MyiHeart.com.

column1: Mashup: Skype Mood Message to Twitter
column5: This tool, smitter, will post your Skype Mood Message to Twitter after you change your Skype Mood Message. It also writes to a local file to keep a history of your Skype Mood Messages.
Joobel search for local jobs. In German.
This Google Map shows the path of solar eclipses across Earth’s surface. The northern and southern limits of a solar eclipse path are plotted in pink while the central line is blue.
The website is always up-to-date with real estate listings from Miami to Maine. The website uses Google Base listings and provides a property location context using Google Maps.
A search engine for ASP.Net-related applications, code samples, tips, tricks, articles and blog posts based on Google Co-op.

earth album is a google maps + flickr mash-up that allows you to tour the world visually via top-rated flickr photos. Visit the red houses of Norway, swing through the mountains of China, then fly south to the icy Antarctic, all with a few clicks.
Comprehensive NYC real estate search site. Includes data on public school information, market data, stats and trends, details about neighbors and neighborhoods, building and neighborhood photos.
For history buffs and school kids, a mashup showing where presidents/first ladies were born. From George Washington through George Bush.
Compare new homes, home designs, builders, land estate, house plans, via Google Maps in Australia.

column1: Mashup: Find Garage Sales by Map
column5: Find garage sales, local estate sales, multi-family yard sales in your area by looking at a map. Plan your trip here by comparing garage sales by location.
Washington DC real estate & Google Maps mashup maps vacant property and past property sales. Over 70,000 sales records are accessible. See what your neighbors paid.
Look for public Flickr photos with this tag-based search.
Flash-based interface for searching for Flickr photos and YouTube videos by tag. Initially created by Ted Patrick for an Adobe Flex demo at Mashup University.
Compare traffic for up to five domains with this mashup of Alexa, Compete or Quantcast.
Digg for must-have products and services.

A real estate search engine that aggregating nearly a million property listings searchable with a GoogleMap-based visual interface. Site has budding online community of buyers, sellers, and service providers.

column1: Mashup: Sunshine Coast BC Community Site
column5: Not an exciting mashup but I use four different APIs to deliver fresh, useful, or interesting content to this British Columbia travel site.
See the most talked about videos...currently tracking YouTube, MySpace and Google Video.
retrievr is an experimental service which lets you search and explore in a selection of Flickr images by drawing a rough sketch. Very interesting.

column1: Mashup: Ease of Doing Business Map
column5: World Bank-produced Google map on doing business in 175 countries. Countries are color-coded for ease of doing business there: easy, moderate, and difficult, in green, yellow and red respectively.
Use Rollyo to roll your own search engine. Create personalized search Rolls, share them, and search others. See Rolls created celebrities and add search tools to your site.
Quickly edit all your online photos from your browser. Web-based way to fix underexposed photos, remove red-eye, or apply effects to your photos. All online.
Search real estate listings with photos and maps. Winner of the Adobe Flex Developer Derby.

CameraPrices reviews, ratings, prices on 1000s of camera products. Browse the directory to find the best deals and cheapest prices. Check out the blog, polls, news, articles, and photography community for more camera information.
Find the best petrol prices in Ireland via this interactive Google Map.

A prediction market for Amazon products. Each new product added becomes a "stock". If a product's Amazon's sales rank improves, its stock price goes up. And vice-versa. Traders buy, sell, short, and cover.
Visitors can add information about prices available in offline shops.

SpicyPipes allows users to create online mashups. The created mashups for personal use and share them with others through tagging. Slideshow greetings, answers, travel guides, file storage, and sharing.
column6: ['Flickr', 'Google AdWords ', 'Google Maps', 'Yahoo Travel', '23', 'Amazon S3', 'Riya', 'Yahoo Answers', 'Yahoo Widgets', 'Yahoo My Web Search', 'Google Client Authentication', 'Google Picasa']

column5: Collection of online maps using Google or Microsoft maps, street level to whole of the continent, including place name and address search, geocoding and link to map service.
Shows all the locations of a chosen physician group. Click on an icon to see a list of the physicians at that location.

This is a Google map of unprotected/open camera streams obtained from Google searches. The IP addresses for each camera's url has been mapped to its Geo-location. Sometimes loads slowly. Some cams NSFW.

column1: Mashup: 10 Top US Cities Travel Guides
column5: Travel guides for 10 top U.S. cities: New York, Boston, Chicago, San Francisco, Orlando, Las Vegas, Atlanta, Dallas, Houston, and Seattle. Each subdomain includes select video guides pulled via the YouTube API.
Nice integration of library data like what you have checked-out or are waiting forinto an automatically updating Google Gadget. Initially for Ann Arbor District Library. Talis mashup contest winner.
Personalized aviation weather configured with your favorite METARs, TAFs, and radar images.
A flight planning tool for pilots based on Google Maps. Shows airports near your current location, with colour coding for weather conditions reported in METARs, as well as TFR outlines.
Save and share your favorite restaurants, or use the tag cloud to see others favorites. In Italian.
Play video-karaokes for the hot 20 songs of the moment. Create your own with our Online Karaoke Creator.
Build a Virtual Pin Map of the places you've been.
Zudos allows you to view the latest social media buzz on any desired topic through a consolidated interface.
Data Mining 101: Finding Subversives with Amazon Wishlists, demonstrates how your wishlists might be used by government agencies to profile you based on the books you read. By Tom Owad.
Yellow-page listings with points-of-interest data plotted on a map.
Find out what major motion pictures are filmed near you. Results are displayed in a Google map. Click on movie names to get movie details or buy it on Amazon.com.
This gadget is to help find properties that are a specified percentage below the average list price for a Zip Code. This is to assist in finding potential investment properties. Uses Truila API.
This nice del.icio.us enhancement allows you to see which of your del.icio.us bookmarks are used most frequently. By DeWitt Clinton.
Maps police, fire and emergency incidents for many areas around the U.S. It displays a national map as well as maps by region and by zip codes. Shows incidents from multiple agencies on one map.

A PowerPoint mixer to select a PowerPoint presentation on the fly from SlideShare. It uses the SlideShare.net API and pretty effects by script.aculo.us and prototype.js to select a random slideshow for a given tag.
Chinese business mashup for the UK. Around 6000 Chinese businesses listed and mapped.
Creative on-demand print service that lets you turn your Flickr photos from virtual content into physical content like all new Mini Cards.
Platial enables people to find, create and use meaningful maps of Places that matter to them.
Shows the last item bookmarked by the blog owner on Del.icio.us the social bookmarking website.
Search San Francisco Bay Area real estate listings on a map. Currently tracking over 36000+ listings in 157 cities in the bay area.

Mashup of Google Maps, Virtual Earth with many other APIs. Ext.js is used to make user interface intuitive. It lets you search for hotels, photos, restaurants, wifi spots, local news/blogs, events, weather, and many other spatial data.
column6: ['Flickr', 'Eventful', 'Google Maps', 'Microsoft Bing Maps', 'YouTube', 'Yahoo Local Search', 'Panoramio', 'Yelp Fusion']

column1: Mashup: Next Meetup.com Event Stats FeedFlare
column5: Displays a blog owners next Meetup.com event, and the number of Yes and Maybe responses received so far.
Rental property statistics for major metropolitan areas.

This web application called the StainedGlass Collage, first detect region of interest in your digital photo and then organize them similar to laying out a stained glass window. It also allow user to download and upload images directly to Flickr site.

VideoTag is a one-player tagging game. Tag some of the funniest YouTube videos, avoid the pitfalls and progress to the next level. See if you can make the top of the leaderboard and become the ultimate video tagger.
Get news, ratings, game schedules and rumors for NBA teams plotted on a map.
Find where the nearest Starbucks is for each of the OnAIR bus tour stops.
Comparison shopping site with deal, rebate and coupon information. Customer reviews and product information from Amazon.com and Epinions.com.
Google Gadget that lets you run Google Map searches directly from your Google homepage.

The goal of Zoomap is to populate maps with user images. Add any image on any place in the world and leave a message in a text bubble. Everything on the map can be viewed by other users, the images can be reused and you can send the location by email.
Use maps to locate professionals and vendors to help organize and provide services for a wedding. You can also create a personal Wedding Atlas to share important information about a bridal party.
A mash-up of the Adobe OnAIR Bus Tour data from onair.adobe.com with this downloadable AIR application.
Map of wine shops in New York City. With brief summaries and links to their web sites.

Phrasr is an interactive web based application that uses Flickr images to illustrate the phrases that users submit. You can choose every image and then publish the entire phrase, which is shown as a personal slide show.

Scenes From the City is a great mashup. Find the locations of iconic Made in NY films with the Yahoo Map made for the 40th Anniversary of the Mayors Office of Film. Lots of ways to search including director and scene type.
An education search tool which enables you to search by: Location, Career, Industry/Salary and provides personalized searches to save for future reference.Utilizes Flickr, Google Maps and YouTube.
Follow the weather, time, and photos from the OnAIR Bus Tour. Watch the animated bus route coordinated with the dials.
Find the closest OnAIR bus stop to where you live and the current weather at that location
Memory game that chooses Flickr pictures as cards, based on a tag you enter.

Helps shoppers capitalize on price guarantees on recent purchases. Add your purchase information and they will watch for price decreases and automatically notify you if price falls below your purchase price.
Maps of breweries and bars across the US. With city-specific maps and directories.
Earth Album is a google maps and YouTube mash-up that allows you to tour the videospace of the world via YouTube tags.
A content enrichment system that allows users to integrate data from two dozen sources.
Real-time visualizations of the stream of information flowing into Flickr. View photos, tags or buddy icons as they are active on the site.
Bookr is a tool to create photobooks using Flickr images. Photobooks may be e-mailed or embedded in blogs.
Full MLS real estate listings using Google Maps. As of October 2006 also offers data provided by the Zillow API.

GuruLib is an attempt to help organize home libraries. GuruLib fetches all cataloging information such as author and actor list, synopsis, genre, front cover etc. Either via Amazon database or from over 530 public or university libraries around the world.

Ever found yourself listening to a song in a restaurant or a club or at any place and don not have access to a PC. You can find out details of the song right away. SMS a few words from the track and we will get back with track, album and artist.

column1: Mashup: Vancouver BC Popular Attractions Map
column5: Maps popular Vancouver British Columbia attractions with links to more information.
Combines digg-like voting system with maps and other utilities for travelers.
A contributor-based wiki for things to do and places to goin and around Boston.
Contextualizing and situating the list of prisons and the human rights abuses in Tunisia. Mashup of database data with Google Maps, YouTube, Flash animations and Yahoo Q Beta search.
Locations of most recent posters to the Twitter social networking site

column1: Mashup: Places of Interest in France
column5: View stores, beaches, apartments, and other French data on a Google map. Lets you select a place to live near places of interest. Click an item to view photographs of the places.
View eBay auctions on a Google Map. Enter search keywords and a zip code to find local auctions.
Ask Vox is a community question and answer website, where users teach Vox, the website character, to answer questions with voice.
Craigslist apartment listings plotted on a map, with answers to real-estate and apartment-related questions for your city.
Appraise your Seattle-area house by seeing prices of recent home sales plotted on this Google Map.
CareerVote is a social rating, review and tagging mashup that allows people to find and share information about the work environment at different companies.
Maps all of the timeshare resorts in Orlando with their contact details.
Enter an artist name and get videos, discography, bio, torrents and related artists
A community mashup where parents can create, review, tag, and map fun places to take their family.
When you gotta go, but you want to find just the right place, then search here at Urinal.net. Lots of photos in the archive. Both US and international.
Internet application helps users create Google Maps with customized points of interest without writing code.
Database with dive centers, dive boats, dive shops around the world.
A community mashup where people can find ratings, reviews, and videos of the latest mobile phones.

column1: Mashup: LOOQ Here, Buy on eBay
column5: Make a broad search first, then filter based on text, price, and other criteria. Can make finding things on eBay faster and easier.
Find places to stay via this interactive map. Hotels in London, Ireland, Canada and US.
Search all single-family homes, condos, townhouses, and commercial properties for sale and for rent in Florida. All properties have both information and photos.

column1: Mashup: Mr. Rebates for Product Research
column5: This mashup uses the Amazon API to give reviews and ratings on thousands of products organized into handy categories ranging from computers, electronics and home goods.
Most recently posted Twitters locations plotted on a map and updated automatically.
Track visitors to your website using Google Maps.
Nice search and visualization tool that lets you surf Flickr's tag space. Flickr tags are keywords used to classify images. Related tags shown based on clustered usage analysis.
Experimental navigation tool for exploring the space of related Flickr tags. Type in one start tag and dive into tag space. Requires Flash 8.

column1: Mashup: PISCO Ecological Data Products Map
column5: This features the ecological datasets of the Partnership for Interdisciplinary Studies of Coastal Oceans. Users can pick an organism and see its distribution and abundance. Users can also view survey site metadata and species lists.

RinkAtlas provides door-to-door directions to ice rinks in North America. The database currently includes over 1,800 ice hockey and figure skating facilities in the 50 U.S. states and Puerto Rico. Rinks in Canada will be added in the future.

column1: Mashup: Best Hospitals for Cancer Treatment
column5: Best American hospitals for Cancer Treatment as mentioned in US News.
Type a word or phrase into this fun Flickr application and it will return a set of images spelling-out that word, ransom-note style.
See the Forbes Magazine list of the Drunkest Cities in America mapped.
See where your friends are located in the UK. Click on the markers to see their details in the information window.
A Google Earth mashup that shows book tours happening around the world.
Search Flickr for geotagged photos and then plot them on a Google Map. Nice nested map-within-a-map.

column1: Mashup: Lodging options in Buenos Aires
column5: Map of hotels, apartments, hostels and spas in Buenos Aires, Argentina, with links to their websites.
Uses Flickr API to do fun stuff with photos. Home of the fd Flickr Toys.
Forbes list of the most Trusted Celebrieties in American. Mapped with links to Google Videos.
Create your own Google Maps with photos, comments, directions.
This lightweight music search page uses the SNOCAP MySpace Search API to display results along with embeddable Flash player.
Search tool for music fans where you can find MP3s, YouTube videos, Flickr images, news, songs, events, blog posts, podcasts, websites, and articles about artists.
A combination of "Hot or Not" with funny dance videos.
Visualize news stories with this application built on the Yahoo! Search API. Hovering your mouse over images shows article snippets. PHP source code available. From Rasmus Lerdorf.
Google Maps and KML news feed.
Dynamic tribute to Kurt Cobain, showing Nirvana live concerts on a Google map by year. Search for videos directly by keywords.
Official Yahoo Map widget for Yahoo Widgets.
A tourism and venue website. Brings together thousands of audio, video, and PDF files about places to visit in over 20 countries. Uses RSS feeds and Google Maps.

Novel use of Yahoo Image Search to test your memory. Type in a search term and 28 tiles appear. Click on tile to see an image and as quickly as possible find the tile with matching image. From Nisse Bryngfors.

column1: Mashup: Best Quality of Living Cities
column5: Map shows locations of cities ranked as having the best quality of living.

Using the SunlightLabs APIs, Kiwini Oe of Clear Ink created info centers on the Second Life Capitol Hill that offer detailed information on members of the U.S. Congress. This links shows you a YouTube video of the mashup.
Local search resource for travellers. Enter your location and type of business or address. Covers wide variety of locations.
Event tickets website. Can view eBay listings on interactive seating maps, and have events that you cannot attend flagged via the Google Calendar API.

The Sky Clock shows what is happening along the ecliptic in the sky over your head right now. Specifically, it shows you where to find the Sun, the Moon, the five planets visible to the naked eye, and four bright stars that happen to travel near them.

A music discovery mashup that merges Last.fm, Audioscrobbler, artists with SeeqPod audio search results for discovering new music based on artists you already know. This version is optimized for the iPhone.
Map of Ireland with drink prices, parking spaces and petrol prices.

Uses the SharedBook Reverse Publishing Platform, multiple streams of data containing the obituary, guest book entries and family photos automatically flow from Legacy.com to SharedBook where the content is mapped into a structured book product.
Surf predictions and forecasts for surfing spots across the globe. Use the Google Maps interface to get a surf forecast for a coastal prediction.
Play a game based on Google Maps. You can create riddles and try to solve riddles created by other people. You get a picture of a place somewhere on Earth and have to find this place.

Uses Google to find out how popular and sexy celebrities are, and shows images from Yahoo Image Search API. Finds celebrities which are similar in popularity and sexiness. Warning: not always safe for work.

A map mashup for the Gold Coast of Queensland Australia, showing accommodation and attractions. Simple application using custom icons, single xml file, selectable grouping. Aims are to build the map content via user submission to the forum on the site.
Generate money on your website or blog with MotionMall's service. Allows you to customize banner ads for your target audience and displays bestselling products using the Amazon API.

column1: Mashup: Oral Histories of Route 66 Map
column5: Jay Crim and Shekar Davarya spent the summer of 2002 driving across the country on Route 66, collecting interviews with the people who live, work and travel on the old road. This multimedia map is the result. Built with the new My Maps service.
Search tips and lifehacks such as 6 ways to..., how to and ... 10 tips. Japanese version is at tips-kensaku.com
The latest web buzz on Premiership football.
Display crisis hotspots on a world map and retrieve latest news on each crisis from Reuters.
This page answers the question: Where can I go for under a certain amount of money? It displays airfares under a user defined amount of money on a Google map.

GIS Jobs Clearinghouse and Google Maps comes together in GIS Jobs Listing Map. This map was developed by terra IMS in collaboration with the GIS Jobs Clearinghouse. Terra IMS geocodes job listings and displays them on a Google Map.
Flight Simulator built using Microsoft Virtual Earth maps.
Dutch mashup that superimposes carnival parade routes on a Virtual Earth map.
MuveQ.com lets you add movies to your Netflix.com or Blockbuster.com queue via SMS text message from your cell phone.
Allows you to create mosaics of photos from Flickr. Each mosaic is one large image composed of small tile images.

Book trends for publishers using the Amazon API. Retrieves current and historic sales rank data for Amazon book titles, displaying trends in graphic and numeric form for each analysis and decision making.
The Amazon API and RSSBus combined to create a wishlist widget. With this widget, not only will people buy you things, but you can get paid when they do.
This mashup combines great motorcycling routes on a map along with route information, trip length, and locations of nearest H-D dealerships and Best Western Hotels.
Resource for hikers that combines Amazon product data with online resources for camping and trail information.
Ransomizr creates a randomly generated font from single-letter Flickr images and allows you to immediately compose and save ransom-letter-style notes.
Search for activities, things to do, recommended eating and cheap lodging for any city in the US. Search from your WAP capable phone.
Fly into a series of locations around the world. Cycles through scenes every 60 seconds. Requires IE plugin.
Full screen, Google Maps real estate portal to find real estate professionals, properties for sale, and home valuation with local agent recommendations.
Dagbladet.no uses Google Maps, global geocoding, ajax and global geocoded weather forecast for this experimental weather service.
Compares relative popularity of spellings or concepts based on web frequency. An experiment in sidesifting the Web for useful patterns of information.
News, pictures, music, videos and gossip about your favorite celebrity. Built on Amazon, eBay, Wikipedia, and Yahoo Search.
Price comparison shopping with experts advice.
Music mashup that allows searching of data from Amazon, news from Yahoo, and blogs via Technorati.
