column5: Find public libraries in the US and Canada. Data for more than 20,000 libraries available. Choose Yahoo or Google Maps.
Panoramic virtual tours presenting historical objects, landscapes, urban areas, hotels, restaurants, entertainment and sport centers etc. In Czech and English.

column1: Mashup: Live Tennis Scores by Phone
column5: Get latest tennis scores on your cell phone using SMS, WAP and email. Use the keyword tennis followed by part of the player name.
XSSDB provides an intelligent way for browsing and learning about different Cross-site scripting, XSS, attack vectors.
Zimride is a carpool and rideshare matching website that uses Facebook profiles and geocoded addresses. Imagine the possibilities.
A Google Maps and Hellenic National Tourist Organization mashup with information about mountain refuges in Greece. With links to tourist site details.
A mashup of Google Maps, geocoder.us, and over 800,000 street level photos arranged by latitude and longitude. Very nice Crusin Mode simulates driving down a given street.
Plazes local search combines Yahoo Local Search and Plazes.com so that you can search your current neighborhood without entering your current location.
Find drink places in the greater Portland, Oregon and Seattle, Washington areas. Includes good listings of brewpubs and vineyards.

The MyDataBus service provides a simple way to store, transfer, and share your files online. Data can include photos, videos, and others. Integrates with social tools like Facebook. Integration with Snipshot allows online photo editing.
View the source location of various podcasts. US and international podcasts listed.
Create personalized T-Shirts with your own coded messages.
MyStoreRewards integrates with the eBay and PayPal API to deliver a turn-key buyer reward program.
Blog that has an earthquake monitor on a Google Map and news feeds.

You click, SpokenBuzz calls you, you record your thoughts, and then your voice appears on the map. Others can reply with their voice and continue the conversation. Discuss restaurants, bars, beaches, whatever you want.
See the path of your network connection using traceroute and this mapping tool. Uses Java applet.

column1: Mashup: Stormberry.tv - Web videos with subtitles
column5: Allows users to add subtitles to web videos and search for related products.

A real time map of where an eBay seller has shipped items. The map provides credibility to small online sellers and gives potential buyers a sense that the seller has conducted business in their geography.

column1: Mashup: MyGeoPosition.com - Geocoding, Geotag- and KML-Creator
column5: Calculate your geoposition by address and create geotags, geo-metatags and kml files for your website, weblog or photo. Use a drag-and-drop marker on the result map to optimize your position. NEW: Reverse lookup - Enter a geocoded URL, see its location.
Allows users of flickr and 23 photo services to mash up their images into an interactive web page with the option of including Google Maps or Second Life Maps as a background.
Japanese mashup combining videos and Google Maps.
Plot, save and share running routes.
A guide to Bed and Breakfasts that makes extensive use of Google Maps.
Shopwiki helps users find the best deals on the internet. Search for products on the go from your cell phone using SMS and WAP. Simply use the keyword shopwiki and get the best deals online.
Good interactive map of the Washington DC Metrorail.

Find out how US Bloggers are feeling today. And which area of US is full of happy bloggers and which sad. BlogUSphere Moods maps the feelings of US Bloggers on the US map, making use of We Feel Fine API, Yahoo Pipes and Google Maps.
An nice explorative Flash-based interface into Flickr photos. With tag search, interestingness sorting, user tabs, and related tags.
Guide to events, attractions and businesses for cities across the United States. Formerly called usguidez.
Google Maps mashup of the Detroit Tigers players and where they are from. Popups include photos and links to detailed stats.
Quintura.com is a visual-based search engine for web discovery and browsing of any web content, including tests, images, videos, and products.
Find good music and drinks in the NYC and NJ areas with the map that plots data from the Crooked Beat venue and calendar database.
Helps image buyers more efficiently find images and image owners to sell them, by accepting payments for them and archiving licenses for public inspection.
Recommendation engine that uses YouTube as a source for videos.
Foodio54 has an editable database of over a half million restaurants that users can rate and review. The site uses collaborative filtering to make restaurant recommendations.
Enter one search and see Web sites, images and videos related to your search term.
A visually rich interactive Flash tool for exploring place based on the geotagged photos at Flickr. Search by user, tag and collection.
Compare prices for products. Read product reviews and articles that are relevant to each category. View coupons, deals, and rebates from major retailers.
Toronto Live Club Hub helps locals and visitors find out where to find live music in the Toronto area via maps and integrated links to club listings.
Discounts and rewards from a wide range of programs including AAA, AARP, Upromise, Ebates, Amex, Visa, Delta SkyMiles, American AAdvantage and more mashed up to a comparison shopping API.

column1: Mashup: One Trick Towns of America
column5: Map of Inc. magazine list of American One Trick Towns. Includes Punxsutawney for Ground Hog Day, the North Pole, Gilroy Garlic Festival, the Most Haunted Town, Paris Texas, and others.

GRNDX, the first Green Index. Similar to a stock market index, but it tracks mentions of certain key green phrases in the media. Lets you gauge how much mindshare certain concepts have and see if they are gaining or losing ground compared to last week.
A local search mashup using your IP address to attempt to fix your position. Includes info about your IP address.
Using Google Maps API plus Google KML API to render my blog in a Geo context.
Soup Soup displays news articles from news sources such as CNN, BBC, FOX News, etc. with related articles from Wikipedia and other sites and photos from Flickr. The system uses Yahoo Pipes.
A mapping tool for property managers that they can add to their site.
Musicr.info is a music portal with images, videos, lyrics, top artists, a tag cloud, and more.
A very fun Flickr game in which you view a set of ten images and try to guess the common tag. Time based scoring.
The latest videos and related details from YouTube, Technorati and Yahoo Search.
TicketObserver compares ticket prices for theme parks in France and Belgium. It will expand soon to the UK and US.
Unusual use of the Google Maps API to control a non-Google map, in this case from the game World of Warcraft. It behaves just a like a Google Map using zoom, pan and drag controls.
Simple Amazon search interface that filters items to show only things eligible for Amazon Prime free shipping.
Backtags.com provides a social popularity ranking based on bookmarks from a range of leading social bookmarking sites.
The New York City streets are full of interesting and potentially useful things that have been thrown out. If you see something good, snap a pic, send to GarbageScout where others can go and get it.
Comprehensive mashup for real-time UK traffic information.
Mashup of Local Halloween Events. Google Maps, Yahoo News, Yahoo Local, Flickr, Upcoming, HostIP.

This Firefox extension allows you to submit the webpage you are viewing to digg, del.icio.us, Facebook, and other places. It also tells you whether the webpage you are on has been dugg and commented on, and how many times it has been saved on del.icio.us.
If you are interested in the game business, you can use the GCDB searching and mapping tools to find companies near you.
A mashup for the ancient Roman road Via Claudia Augusta between Konigsbrunn and Epfach in Germany.
View all Track info, track layouts, and links to track specific information for all 32 NASCAR tracks.
Mashup that helps you discover and share GPS tracks and waypoints on the web quickly and easily.
Searches Google Base and maps vehicle classifieds.
musicmap is a visual music search tool for finding the albums similar to the ones you know.
JobNeters contains a Google Map with jobs based on their cities.
Levi European store locator.

Job seekers can view jobs based on the usual criteria, such as salary, permanent or temp, location etc. and see the results by list or on a Virtual Earth map. Clicking on a location reveals the available jobs in that area.
The TurnHere video service chronicles different neighborhoods and places across the country through the use of Internet video films. This map plots their locations.
Find Nissan Dealers in the UK with this mashup.

Genuinely useful mashup that can help you determine if you are paying too much in rent. Enter an address, apartment size, and rent. It maps nearby units and shows a meter of your price versus min, max and average.

Find Tesco store locations on a Virtual Earth map of the UK with an optional satellite image overlay. Hover the mouse over a location to get directions, or click on the name of the store to view its address, phone number and store hours.
Desktop application for managing photos on the Smugmug service.
A mashup site where you can leave your digital footprints that are of emotional value to you. You can post photos and videos by form upload, email or MMS.
Mapping application for locating real estate listings in the UK.
Custom classifieds service includes user stores, streaming Google Earth integration, ad syndication, photo hosting, and other features.
Mac desktop application for batch uploading of files to various photo services including Flickr, Smugmug, and Textamerica.

column1: Mashup: Mobile Search on Urban Dictionary
column5: Search for slang definitions on Urban Dictionary using your mobile phone. Use SMS, WAP and Email. You can also use IM clients like Yahoo, MSN and AOL.

This website uses Virtual Earth mapping technologies and real-time GPS location data to display the current locations of all ferryboats in the fleet. Click on the thumbnail map of a specific route to view a larger map with current ship status.
Mitsubishi dealer locator for the UK.
Windows desktop application for managing photo scrapbooks. With photo service upload capabilities.
Map of the Top 10 paid women as reported by Fortune Magazine.
Kent County Council. View road traffic status and live camera feeds in the UK.
Real estate search for Southern California. Search for properties meeting specific criteria. Hover over a specific property on the map to reveal address and price.
The eMiniMall advertising banners are built on top of the shopping.com APIs.
Nearly 200 Hindu temples in America on Google Maps. The site title, Stuladarshanam, means birds eye view in Sanskrit.
A Google Maps interface to a database of thousands of hang gliding and paragliding sites around the world, with a feed to show the same in Google Earth.

column1: Mashup: Boots Optician Store Locator UK
column5: Use this interactive map to find Boots Optician stores in the UK.
Great for runners, hikers, bicyclist and anyone else interested in how far they ran, walked, biked, or traveled. Map, save, find, and share your routes.

CarePages.com allows members to move the content contained on a site including message board comments, updates regarding care and prognosis and photographs into a CarePages Keepsake Book that can be purchased immediately or personalized further.

Golfing enthusiasts can search for golf courses on a Virtual Earth map. Select a course and reserve tee times. This mashup combines data from Cybergolf, weatherforyou.com, and other sources to provide a comprehensive golf planning experience.
Innovative prototype for exploring Flickr photos. Point the application at a feed, like CNN, it then renders the news in photos by matching tagged photos to words from the news.

column1: Mashup: auctionReminder - eBay Reminders in Google Calendar
column5: auctionReminder is a simple tool to add reminders about ending eBay auctions to a Google Calendar.

Mobypicture enables you to add postings with pictures to Twitter and also get these directly posted to your Flickr-album. You can use it from your mail client or directly from your phone, so you can show your friends what your doing instead of typing it.
Like TinyUrl.com but for Google Maps, for example http//useamap.com/lotto . You select the tag name. One click to create a map. No login needed. Free. Just launched on 9th October.
A stylish mashup that helps you find information on gas prices, movies, restaurants, traffic, local events, WiFi locations, driving directions, and more on a Virtual Earth map.
A travel blog where travellers can create blogs about their journeys and map their travels.
Use this comprehensive index from HDTV Magazine to find television stations broadcasting in HDTV for all major US markets. Map gives details by station including power information.
Walk Score shows you a map of what is nearby and calculates a Walk Score for any property. Buying a house in a walkable neighborhood is good for your health and good for the environment.
Maps US IT contract jobs matching keywords. Search companies, rate companies, view company ratings, save searches, save jobs, attach notes to saved jobs, and add private jobs.

Helps you find accommodations, events, activities, and things to do when planning a vacation or outing in Washington State. Locations and details of each activity are superimposed on a Virtual Earth map.
Wiki and mapping site allowing scuba divers to share their favorite dive sites and advice. Good interface.
Share MusicMobs or Last.fm playlists in Rhapsody. Uses XSPF, XML Shareable Playlists Format for playlist integration. This links to MusicMob blog post with examples.
MyBikramYoga.com is dedicated in bringing you the latest in the Bikram yoga community, news, blogs, images and videos.
MyToGo allows any phone to call Skype names for free or call telehone numbers using Skype from any phone at Skype rates. No client software on phone is required. Works with iPhones.
Worldwide vacation rental listings direct from owners.

Create time-based subtitles for any YouTube video, a la closed captioning. These captions become publicly accessible, and visitors to the site can browse the set of videos with captions. Think of it as a subtitle graffiti wall for YouTube.
This nice graphing application shows you the count of del.icio.us tags applied to a given URL over time. By Terrell Russell.
Compares all 6 Amazon international stores, adds shipping to the user country, using user local currency, as updated daily using a webservice, and keeps a price evolution chart.
Aggregated feed of all Linkedin RSS feeds. Mashes up RSS feed questions and website published answers.
After you have logged in to MapYourBuddies, this mashup will display your friends from Facebook on a Google Map and give gift recommendations from Amazon based on your friends favorite music.
Hangman game for Flickr tags. Guess all the letters of a tag and see 4 photos.
A lightweight Flickr viewer. You can search and browse photos by users, contacts, photosets, tags, or groups. If the photo is geotagged, it can also be mapped.
Use this album maker to build an album and a slideshow of your Flickr photos. It can generate HTML code for you to embed to your blog or web site.
View radar and cloud cover superimposed on an animated Virtual Earth map. Adjust the degree of transparency for the weather data to see more or less of the underlying map.
Find Sony stores in Germany with this Multimap mashup.
Enter a word and watch the flickr photo stream. Click to interrupt stream and try another word.
An Australian Real Estate Search engine. Found results are displayed in Google Earth and on the Google Map.
Zeiss European store finder for Germany.

Spotstory is a place where people can share and discover interesting, but often overlooked, locations. Spotstory can be thought of as wiki for place, combined with mapping, photo sharing, social networking, and more.
Flash application developed using Flickr and Yahoo Map APIs.
Jorg Pfeiffer is on a road trip from Berlin to Southeastern Europe for the German magazine Der Spiegel. Users can post ideas on what topics to cover and places to visit. In German.
Interactive map that can be used to find a veterinarian near home or while traveling by Pets Best.
Meta search engine mashup built as a high-school project. It allows you to create your own search engine where you can choose from 30+ sources you want to include in your results.
Converts latitude-longitude from a mouse click to a full address.
WeddingWire uses GoogleMaps to mashup thousands of wedding vendors locations such as florists, photographers, DJs, etc. in the US.

column1: Mashup: Live U Mich Bus Maps
column5: Creative use of GPS, mapping and Ajax technology to show the current location of buses in the University of Michigan area.
Recent school shootings mapped. Compiled from infoplease.com
Dutch mashup combining Maps with demographic information.

column1: Mashup: Barnard Marcus UK Real Estate
column5: Barnard Marcus UK property and branch locator. Search for real estate to buy or rent.
Track the current status of all MLB games with a single keyword. Simply use SMS or WAP and use keyword scoresmlb.
Canadians, find your ideal urban apartment. Covers most major cities including Toronto, Vancouver, Montreal and Halifax.
A set of graphic visualisations for your del.icio.us account that allow you to browse, search and select tags, as well as viewing posts matching them.
See hotel availabilities and reserve a room in the principality of Andorra, which is on the border of France and Spain.

On your WAP capable devices or your PC, simply go to 411Sync.com and use the keyword razorgator to view all the latest tickets available. These tickets may be for sports, converts or events. Purchase hard to get tickets at the last moment.
Combines YouTube videos, Flickr photos, Last.fm albums and Amazon books, grouped by Wikipedia category.
Profileomat is a shareable Profile Aggregator that lists all your personal Websites, Social Networks, Blogs, Contact Info, Photo Albums and other Profiles in a box. Formerly called linkmybox.com

I was thinking about how many places who sell pizza are around me. I put only fresh pizzas cooked in the place, not frozen ones. Three icons: restaurant, stand, shop. I stop this thing to places 500 meters around my house: there are 40, it is weird...
Sophisticated interface for exploring the birds of North America. Combination of USGS and Audubon Society data. Required Flash 8.
A 360 degree panorama journey through Prague. Over 400 locations and 800 panoramas. Now with navigation in 18 languages.
TripAdvisor has mashed up millions of hotel reviews with Google maps for a hotel search that sorts by user-generated popularity index and allows filtering by price and availability.
Provides an overview of travel highlights around the world using interactive maps with destinations such as cities, beaches, national parks and cultural sites.

Customizable widgets that combine maps with photos and points of interest like restaurants, hotels, attractions, and shops for 200 destinations throughout the US, Europe, Canada, Australia, and New Zealand.
Private website using Weatherbug to get information about local weather and change the appearance of parts of the site respectively.
Take full 360 degree photo tours of popular Toronto landmarks like the Air Canada Centre, Rogers Centre, and CBC HQ. Good quality, large images.
A Google Map showing the headquarters of the 100 best US companies to work for as ranked by Fortune Magazine. Marker popups give details on each.

myVidster is a social video bookmarking and gallery service. Collect all your videos in one place, share your collections with friends or a large audience, and explore what other people are collecting.
Real estate website that uses Bigtribe-Geohana to display property locations on a Google Map and drive the display of information related to the locations as they are selected.
Feed of the latest stuff from amazon.com with links to Netflix, Blockbuster, or other vendors for rental and purchase.
Free things to see, get and do in London.

Doctor Who - unlike Star Trek which always used the same rock for its location filming - was surprisingly varied in its choice of quarries. This mashup shows where they are all and includes a kml for Google Earth.
A Widgetbox widget that uses Bigtribe, Geohana and Google Maps to create an embeddable restaurant locater widget.
Discover Melbourne Australia with LocalHero, combines local search with an ajax interface. Integrated wiki functionality, or double-click the map to add content.
Extremely basic street-to-GMaps lookup for Ireland. Proof of concept only. Uses Lycos Route Planner for geocoding to street level only.
Tour of California Cycling Blog covers 100+ mile bike rides. GPS satellite data, route profiles, pictures, and more information is available.
A Widgetbox widget that uses Bigtribe, Geohana and Google Maps to create an embeddable golf course locater widget.
Create map riddles for your friends and the world.
GoOffCampus.com is a resource intended to help students find rental properties close to campuses all over the US.
Uses the Amazon API and an Ajax-style UI to retrieve CD/DVD covers from the Amazon catalog. The second version of Albumart.org adds music, video, and lyric search, in addition to albumart search.
Get the latest StumbleUpon Buzz on your mobile phone using the keyword sumobile. Users can use this keyword and request information using SMS, WAP or Email.
Racoon The Searcher is search and subscription system that collects information about all government procurement in Russia. In Russian.
Park reviews for national and state parks. Includes option to mark favorite places to share with others.

column1: Mashup: Ming Campbell for MP Campaign Map
column5: Maps the speeches, messages of support and upcoming meetings, from www.flocktogether.org.uk, of Ming Campbell MP, candidate to lead the UK Liberal Democrats.
Visual Search Maps powered by Google, TRYNT and Yahoo.
column6: ['del.icio.us', 'Google Search', 'Yahoo Search', 'Yahoo Video Search', 'Yahoo Image Search', 'Yahoo Related Suggestions', 'Trynt']

column5: Search the friends lists of your friends to find people who should be on your own list.
Displays Google search terms in a tag cloud. Uses Yahoo Term Extraction API to group terms together. Greasemonkey script available.

Using information gathered from newspapers, planning board agendas and other sources, plots of new retail developments of several national retailers such as Wal-Mart, Target, and Kohls using a Google Maps interface.

Helps users find RSS feeds and autogenerates OPML files. Uses Windows Live Search API. Facilitates selecting feeds from root weblogs or comments feeds per user selection with support for international markets.
See locations of the venues for the 2006 events with good links to details from the official Olympics site. From Remo Madella.
FoxyMap is a Google Gadget which allows you to monitor the locations of speed traps. Those locations are set via mobile tagging by the users of the mobile application FoxyTag.

column1: Mashup: Dutch Cultural History at Buurtatlas
column5: Combination of Mediawiki and Google Maps to manage location based data about Dutch cultural heritage.

column1: Mashup: Online Bed and Breakfast Directory
column5: Online bed and breakfast directory with listings worldwide, travel gift certificates and Blog.
Early Miser is a mashup built on top of Shopping.com, Yahoo Shopping, Amazon, and Ebay. It offer comparison shopping, custom product lists, custom product feeds and tagging.

column1: Mashup: Search Yahoo Answers by Phone
column5: Search Yahoo Answers using SMS and WAP. Send your question and get back a list of related questions and answers. When you use SMS, you will get back a list of questions that match your search criteria along with a WAP url that you can visit for answers.
Mashes up MLS home listings with bank-owned property records to flag active listings as bank-owned. Allows the bargain-hunter buyer to identify homes for sale owned by a bank.
Upcomingscrobbler brings together Last.fm and Upcoming.org to tell you where you can see your favourite bands perform live.
Create your own slideshow and let it run on your Vista Sidebar. Expands on undocking from sidebar. Multiple instances can play different slideshows. Keeps settings after Windows restart.
EventPedia provide user with events information ranging from festival to sport events on USA according to date and addresses.
This tool shows you restaurant ratings around your location. If you want to go beyond your normal lunch places, this is a great app.
Mashup created with the Eddy Framework and Yahoo APIs that displays the latest technology news from PC Magazine, The BBC, HowStuffWorks and Major Geeks in a tabular structure.

If you ever had problems ordering camera supplies from a vendor in NYC, then this map might be of interest. It plots the locations, along with photos and comments, of dozens of vendors. Not always reputable ones.
There are literally thousands of hotels across the world employing green policies of some kind, but these hotels truly represent the best of green culture.

A promo site for Penguin books, tracking the tour of a woolly mammoth across the UK. Vistors are invited to share their photos of the mammoth via Flickr, and post opinions. Photos are referenced by city, opinions by postcode and presented via GoogleMaps.
Tubarati allows you to get the latest YouTube videos based on the most popular posts by bloggers around the world, using Technorati tags.

This Netvibes module searches for audio, video, photo or document files from your Orb account matching a search string. Clicking on results can play corresponding video or audio stream, open picture in a new window or download the document.
Search through MLS listings in the SF Bay Area via this Google Maps mashup.
Flowser is graphical Amazon Browser. Type in a product name and see a visualization of the search results by product type.
A new developing comparison shopping mashup using Shopping.com API.
TagCloud is an automated Folksonomy tool that searches RSS feeds you specify, extracts keywords and ranks them via font size in a visual cloud.
Users of Stikkit can now use text messaging to send Stikkit notes to their account. You can also retrieve the next to do, or calendar item.
Visualize the most important incoming links for any URL. Visualizations can be generated using Yahoo! Inbound Links or Google PageRank.
Map based search for lowest petrol price and station locations around Western Australia.
Puts Skype Presence icons on a Google Map. From Japan thus can be slow in US.
Slick podcast app that combines band event data from Eventful with MP3 tracks. Type in a city, get MP3s, discover a band you like, and go see them.
Rate what you ate. A community-based restaurant review guide where users can rate the restaurant and the food. Everything is contributed by users including restaurants, menus, tags, links, etc.

Junkdepot is a free and easy way to sell all your junk. You can also find great items other people want to sell. Your listings are syndicated to other classified sites and you can find listings near you on our Google map.
Search for health-related products on Drugstore.com using SMS, WAP, or Email. Compare prices of different products. Type drugstore followed by the product name to view search results.
Chart your love compatibility with up to five potential mates.
Mashup of events from Upcoming.org with local parking facilities. Advanced reservations are also possible at some locations.
Uses Technorati and Feedburner APIs to rank Philippine blogs.
Treemap visualizations based on del.icio.us tag data or user data.
Enter your Youtube username and press the button to create an RSS feed with embedded movies of your Youtube Favorites.
Windsurfing and Kitesurfing locations around the world, using a Google Map as the index for a Wiki.
A do-it-yourself Goolge Maps site. You can create maps, upload photos, add comments and ratings. Explore maps created by other users.
An interesting way to look at real estate in the UK.
Local search of places close to the subway stations in Sao Paulo, Brazil.
A sufer blog that hosts a surf spot locator that uses Google Maps and Flickr API.
Free searchable collection of stock photography powered by Wikimedia Commons.

column1: Mashup: Dude Where is My Used Car
column5: Find the perfect used car near you with this nicely done mashup of eBay Motors and Google Maps. One of the finalists in the MashupCamp competition.

Gridmarker.com is a free place to store, share, view, and search for your favorite locations in Second Life. You can also find new places to explore by viewing and searching favorite locations of other users.

column1: Mashup: All of Ibiza from one Google Map
column5: IbizaA-Z.com and Ibiza Now Magazine. Everything from one Google Map.
Find and map a variety of local information including blog posts, art gallery reviews, real estate listings, police reports.
Gives an RSS feed of who from your top 50 artists in last.fm are coming to your town.
Mashing up the Google Feed API and Windows Live Search for isfeed: access to RSS files, this provides a river of news reading experience for recent posts around any keyword.
Displays Portland TriMet MAX light rail lines and stations on Google Maps.
A memorial mashup for the victims of Virginia Tech.

Multi-Search uses Pipes, BBC News, Yahoo Search and Term Extraction APIs, and the Google Blog Search. We start with BBC news stories and excerpts, gather terms, find blog entries through Google, and then guess the feed URL using Yahoo Search.
Find pick-up spots using this collaborative map.
A web site about Nokia that use Google Maps, Search and Video APIs.

column1: Mashup: SeLoger for French Home Prices
column5: French real estate prices. Charts, maps, median prices. Time line of prices over time. Housing data from France.
Very cool overlay of NOAA nautical charts on top of Virtual Earth maps engine. Charts can be made translucent.
View locations made famous in the Seinfeld sitcom. Includes the Soup Nazi, the Diner, and Nathans Coney Island.

column1: Mashup: Formula One Grand Prix Circuit
column5: Displays all Formula One Grand Prix Circuits raced from 1950 to 2007.

Introducing a different way to shop the eBay listings for the most searched for products being auctioned. AuctionCloud shows popular keywords used by eBay users when searching listings. Real estate section uses Zillow API for zestimates.
Uses Yahoo Search and del.icio.us to search for articles on Wikipedia, show them inline and allow instant bookmarking. Tutorial on how this was built at kentbrewster.com

column1: Mashup: International AIDS Candlelight Memorial Map
column5: On Sunday 21 May 2006 thousands of communities around the world will come together in solidarity to light candles and remember those who have been affected by HIV AIDS. This map plots those locations.
Listings of items discounted by 50 percent or more on Amazon.com in US, UK, France and Germany.
Search Yelp.com from your cell phone using SMS, WAP and Email. Simply send us what you are searching for and where. Within a few seconds, you will obtain user recommended results.
Get detailed weather information from hundreds of weather stations via this rich map interface built on the Weatherbug API, Microsoft Virtual Earth and Flash popups.
Just enter your favorite musical artist and discover all related artists. It has never been easier to find good bands. Youtube videos and amazon links included.
Mac OS X 10 Spotlight plug-in to search del.icio.us
A Mac OS X desktop application that lets you browse your del.icio.us accounts.
Loc Amigos helps you find your friends all over the web. It will match up friends in your address books with their profiles across lots of social networking sites like MySpace, Flickr, and others.
The Apprentice on NBC starts a new season this week. This maps shows the hometown of each contestant on Google Maps with their current status of either Active or Fired.

Tracegps.com lets you search and share your favorite outdoor trail by importing and exporting GPS data and Google mapping them. Use it to send files of your walk, bike ride or running trail or find a new hike or city tour nearby.

Giveness is a social network for philanthropy. Charities can create their own communities to connect with their supporters and fundraise online. When a user purchases a product through Giveness, 100 percent of the commissions generated will be donated.
An auction sharing community where users find, share, and rate interesting eBay auctions.

Freeform radio station WFMU is holding a pledge drive marathon in which anonymous points are automatically added to the world map when its globe-spanning listeners submit their pledges. Listeners can also add comments.
Search and view outdoor geo-tagged live webcams. Rated and shared by users.
A look at the 25 most unsafe cities in America.
Converts virtually any URL into Adobe PDF. From 9-Interactive.

GCC 2007 allows participants to track their progress on a virtual journey around the globe. The journey is measured by steps, which are tracked on pedometers. The solution manages 161 locations in a CMS to track and zoom between each one.
Utility application built using the eBay API that allows you to display your eBay auctions on your blog or website.

column1: Mashup: Lord of the Rings Maps
column5: Lord of the Rings Online game map using Google Maps technology.
Google News Feed Reader for the Apple iPhone.

A real estate site that gives you quick and easy access to information on any property in the US. eppraisal.com data is updated daily and pulls from a database of about 70 million homes. Integrated maps and estimated home valuations.
Use this handy Jacktracker mashup to follow the TV show 24. Incorporates images and various plot details. Uses the Wayfaring.com features such as discussion boards for each waypoint.

A Mozilla Firefox extension allowing users to view what music their facebook friends listen to and how similar their tastes are. View what music their Facebook users have recently being listening to on Last.fm and what their current chart is.
A mashup app at uses Grazr to interact with Rhapsody, making for a smoother experience than the Rhapsody default UI. You will need a Rhapsody account to stream any audio.
Geocode addresses in bulk, plot multiple locations to a single map. Built using Yahoo Maps and Yahoo Geocoding API.
Add, or just read, your daily horoscope, zodiac bio or chinese zodiac bio to your Blog, MySpace or Web Page.
iPhoneRevu is a map and list view of Yelp Reviews formated for the iPhone. iPhoneRevu is a Yelp front-end for the iPhone.

Best beaches, diving, parks, pictures from the island of Okinawa, Japan. See virtual images, panoramas, and aerial photographs of places to visit. Pictures link to reviews, driving directions, maps, and slideshows.

column1: Mashup: Wasting Away Superfund Toxic Legacy
column5: From The Center for Public Integrity, Wasting Away is an authoritative report on the EPA that includes an original accounting of the companies responsible for many of polluted sites in America, as well as an array of maps that show where these sites are.
Follow the progress of CBS television show The Amazing Race via the Goolge Map mashup.
Review mashup for new Turkish President Mr. Abdullah Gul. You can enter the location where you live and put reviews on the map about Mr. Abdullah Gul.
Maps, videos, photos, news, social networking for the action sports community for riders, skateboarding, snowboarding, skiing, surfing, bmx, mountain biking, motocross and wakeboarding.
psynchr is a Flash based web service to view multiple photosets. You can synchronize multiple photosets on flickr.
Floating Link Preview is a tool which displays thumbnail image preview of the web page related to the link underneath your mouse cursor. Uses data from from thumbshots.org.

Private intranet and outward facing website for the community living at the former Hartley Jam Factory, London. This website gives local residents a web presence of their own and aggregates all resident blogs into a jam-factory-specific portal.
Kids party entertainer and venue mashup--aggregates photos, videos and reviews, and helps parents find the right kids entertainment within their budgets.
column6: ['Google Maps', 'Yahoo Local Search', 'Google Calendar', 'Facebook', 'Google Base', 'Google Checkout']

column1: Mashup: Business of Baseball on Google Maps
column5: Google Maps Mashup of Forbes data on the Most valuable teams in MLB. Also includes Yahoo Sports MLB RSS feeds.
An online image editor that integrates nicely with Flickr.
Mashup of the Penn State campus map with Google Maps. You can search for a building on the map.
A cycle route in to Paris from Charles de Gaulle Airport. Uses Google Maps markers which also display route directions and are linked with photographs taken on the ground.

column1: Mashup: Student Housing Info at UC Davis
column5: Rental listings are shown on a Google map according to the filter you select. You can switch to Satellite view and zoom in to see the actual places and their surroundings on the map.

Combines the del.icio.us online bookmarking service with Google Mobile. This allows you to browse through mobilized versions of your del.icio.us bookmarks from your phone browser or other limited-display browsers
Images, videos, and news about your favorite celebrities from Yahoo, YouTube and Technorati.

Search Zillow for estimates from your cell phone using SMS, WAP and Email. Configure alerts and get notified real time as estimates change. Simply use the keyword zillow and provide the address of the property.
Birth Cities of Oscar winning Best Actors and Actresses mapped out on Google Maps. Covers from 1928 to present.
Enter the name of digg user and see who is digging them. Can be used to highlight the issue of digg cabals and people who only digg each other.
MeteoStone is an experimental project for people to collect and share meteorological data about weather all over the world.
Map of Toronto lofts for sale

column1: Mashup: Where I Had My First Kiss
column5: Share your fondest or worst memories of your first kiss on this community and mapping site. Top level map shows most recently added kiss locations on a world map.

column1: Mashup: Cool Bars, Restaurants and Clubs
column5: Google map and bars, lounges, restaurants and clubs etc. Links to reviews. Venues have map with nearby venues. Site also has a Mapchat mashup mixing maps and chat and a Twitter mashup in the members section, showing your status and pic in your profile.
One Stop Cottage, the Holiday Cottage Search Engine, is a very fast way to find your UK holiday cottage. It quickly searches over 40,000 cottages from 35 companies.
MapLib.net is a free service that allows users to upload pictures that may be as large as 6000 by 6000 and create their own custom Google maps.

Map mashup for mobile phones. FONFinder produces a mobile-friendly XHTML page with a map of the nearest FON hotspots based on a street address. Maps are adjusted in size for each particular mobile phone model.
One-line JavaScript include gets you instant social networking via Twitter.
User driven search where users contribute listings, reviews, pictures, tags, and more. Toronto is first city setup, includes mapped traffic conditions.

Camera shoppers, this site offers user consumer reviews and ratings from multiple sources. Also on this page are live price comparisons to help the user find the best deals on the web together with live ebay listings for the camera of their choice.

This word-hunting Google Gadget has been XXtended with the UrbanDictionary and WordNet APIs. Now you can guess slang, proper nouns, and more. Plus, read the definitions of every word you guess correctly.
View freelance jobs from Indeed.
A meta-search engine using tagging services such as RawSugar, delicious, and Technorati

Get stock price, percentage change, 52 week range, EPS, PE ratio and market cap for any stock on the go. Simply use the keyword summary followed by the stock ticker symbol, e.g. AAPL, SUNW, AMZN, GOOG etc. Use from SMS, WAP or Email

Canadian apartment, house and condo locater service with a Google Map of rental listings. See comprehensive listings of apartments and houses for rent including photo galleries, a searchable map and amenity details.

Virtual Earth Mashup to help find sports location and event in your area. You can find out about the sports you are interested in and event arrange a meeting of your own at your favourite location. Make new friends who do the same sports as you.
Flickr Tool developed using Flickr and YahooMap REST APIs. This is an Adobe AIR version of MyFlickrTool.
Content based visual image search application for Flickr. Look for an image you like, then Find Similar photos either by subject matter mode or color and texture mode.
Exact distance pedometer using Google Maps, built by a marathon runner.
DuggBack is a service that lets you quickly find all the available mirrors and web caches for a popular Digg story.
All Tchibo shopping offers in a tiny gadget. Never miss a bargain. Supports Tchibo.co.uk, Tchibo.eu, Tchibo.de, Tchibo.at, Tchibo.ch and Tchibo.nl.
Compare book prices before you buy with this handy multiple book price comparison service. You can even feed it your wishlist and get comparisons on them all automatically.
Social networking travel websites that creates personalized recommendations for each user based on user interests and user ratings. Uses geotagged Flickr photo stream and Google maps.
This shows photos of Flickr in Google Maps API Interface, not on map. You can search by tag, text and username.
Podcast transcript search and transcription service built using the Amazon Mechanical Turk API.

World news streaming TV mashup with Google Maps. Watch live world news TV from various TV channels like CNN, BBC, Sky News, ABC News Now, CCTV-9 China, Iran PressTV, France24, CNN IBN India, and Russia Today. Windows Media player required.

The most lovable pooch in the UK is collared up and barking at the door, ready to take you on a mashed-up guided tour of United Kingdom towns and villages. It is built on an ASP.NET 2.0 and SQL Server 2005, and uses APIs from Flickr and Eventful.
Displays book sales on an interactive map.

Popular urls to the latest web buzz. Combines over 15 concensus filters into a one-page view. Good looking, Ajax-ish interface. Includes Digg, Flickr, BoingBoing, NewsVine, del.icio.us, Reddit and others.

column1: Mashup: Small Yahoo Maps in Flex
column5: Demonstrates the workaround provided by Yahoo for using Maps in Flex 2. Uses some sample code as base and adds some simple features like plotting geoRSS, regular RSS, and traffic and weather by zip code.
Mashup of Citysearch and Google Maps to help find the best restaurants, hotels, nightlife, shopping and services in major US cities as voted on Citysearch.com.

column1: Mashup: Google Maps to Browse Warcraft Cards
column5: Google map mashup with cards from the World of Warcraft card game. Browse around the screen, zoom in, and explore all the Heroes of Azeroth cards.
Retailer of overstocks and closeouts uses the Google Checkout API.
Get live weather information from MSN on your mobile phones using WAP, SMS, or Email. Type msnweather followed by a zip code. Get weather updates within seconds.

LazyLibrary lets you find books on any topic without having to worry about high page counts. If it is over 200 pages, you will not even see it. Read all about anything, in less time, for usually less money.

Turtilla is an online service which allows you to search and filter content related to your interests. This content is captured from a large variety of sources. The generated results can be converted to an RSS feed.

Track your packages with Google Maps and RSS feeds! Track UPS, FedEx, USPS, and DHL. PackageMapping.com really works and is free to the public. See where your package is as it makes its way across the map. Check it out and bookmark it!
Bookmark the world from your mobile phone. It is Sharewhere.
Two-player plug-in game for Yahoo Messenger. Finish the round with fewer shots than the other player to win. There are 50 levels in the game.
The Weekend Warrior Hike Finder for Los Angeles and surrounding areas. Warning, can load slowly.
Nationwide bar, night club, and restaurant reviews. Use this map based search engine to find nightlife across the country.
Visits famous places through Virtual Earth and Google Maps. See Related Flickr photos.
Discover restaurants around where you live.
CNN Money list of the top 10 most expensive colleges in the United States. Not necessarily the ones you would expect.
A site is designed to help anyone thirsty for a proper pint to sort through the many pubs and night-spots of Dublin. Expansive, up-to-date database.
Show in real time ultralight aircraft position on google maps, you can also see the cockpit. You can show your plane too.
Guide to Bed and Breakfasts and hotels in France.

A site that generates code to embed maps created using the My Maps service of Google into websites and blogs. A range of style and presentation options are available to customize map appearance. Users can share maps they create in the library of maps.
On-demand service offering management infrastructure and community building tools for API providers. Uses the Amazon S3 and EC2 APIs as part of their infrastructure.
Browse landmarks and other locations in London with this application that combines Google Earth, Google Maps and Wikipedia.
Breaking news and colorful commentary every few minutes, 24-7.

All of preciseNews for Flash RSS users with SpringWidgets.
Nice exploratory interface for finding holiday homes and tourist attractions across Europe.
Waterloo Student Housing to help college and university students find rental housing and sublets. Combines UW housing database with Google Maps.
Displays all Montreal subway statons and lines. Markers are placed very accurate. Can display lines separately.
Displays Amtrak rail routes and stations on Google Maps.
Breaking news in pictures every few minutes. Featured stories are ripped from the headlines, using Netvibes UWA.
A Google map that plots The New York Times column 36 Hours. This column offers a weekend-long itineraries different North American cities. Click markers to browse columns from the past 3 years.
Consolidates different Web components for college students. Contains Google search, video and local search, local businesses, maps, news feeds, professor searches, local drink specials, and games.
Site aggregating breaking science, technology news and colorful commentary every few minutes.
